SIMPLE: deny
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deny
<hw>De*ny"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Denied</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Denying</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>denien</ets>,
<ets>denaien</ets>, OF. <ets>denier</ets>, <ets>deneer</ets>, F.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧nier</ets>, fr. L. <ets>denegare</ets>; <ets>de-</ets> +
<ets>negare</ets> to say no, deny. See <er>Negation</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To declare not to be true; to gainsay; to contradict;
-- opposed to <xex>affirm</xex>, <xex>allow</xex>, or
<xex>admit</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ We <xex>deny</xex> what another says, or we
<xex>deny</xex> the truth of an assertion, the force of it, or the
assertion itself.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To refuse (to do something or to accept something);
to reject; to decline; to renounce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧If
you <xex>deny</xex> to dance.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To refuse to grant; to withhold; to refuse to
gratify or yield to; <as>as, to <ex>deny</ex> a request</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Who finds not Providence all good and wise,⟦br⟧
Alike in what it gives, and what <qex>denies</qex>?</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To some men, it is more agreeable to <qex>deny</qex> a vicious
inclination, than to gratify it.</q> <rj><qau>J. Edwards.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To disclaim connection with, responsibility for, and
the like; to refuse to acknowledge; to disown; to abjure; to
disavow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The falsehood of <qex>denying</qex> his opinion.</q>
<rj><qau>Bancroft.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou thrice <qex>denied</qex>, yet thrice beloved.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To deny one's self</b></col>, <cd>to decline the
gratification of appetites or desires; to practice
self-denial.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let him <qex>deny</qex> himself, and take up his cross.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xvi. 24.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deny</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Deny
<hw>De*ny"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To answer in the negative; to
declare an assertion not to be true.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then Sarah <qex>denied</qex>, saying, I laughed not; for she was
afraid.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xviii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Denyingly</ent>⟦br⟧
